This article reviews general practices and state-of-the-art inoculum expansion methods for recombinant mammalian cell lines. Suspension cell lines are the main focus due to their predominant current and anticipated future usage in large scale biomanufacturing. Conventional inoculum expansion methods are discussed including small scale flasks and seed bioreactors. Disposable technologies and approaches for time reduction during this incoulum expansion step are reviewed, as it is typically a time consuming phase of large scale manufacturing. Technology transfer and the influence of cell bank quality on successful vial thaw and expansion are alo addressed. 


Keywords: 

recombinant cells; 
mammalian cell culture; 
vial thaw; 
inoculum; 
inoculum expansion; 
seed bioreactor; 
cell bank; 
biomanufacturing
